    <div xml:id="PN345">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kaḷiṟaṇaippak kalaṅkiṉa kāa</l>
<l>tērōṭat tukaḷkeḻumiṉa teruvu</l>
<l>māmaṟukaliṉ mayakkuṟṟaṉa vaḻi</l>
<l>kalaṅkaḻāaliṟ ṟuṟai kalakkuṟṟaṉa</l>
<l>teṟaṉmaṟava riṟaikūrtaliṟ</l>
<l>poṟaimalintu nilaṉṉeḷiya</l>
<l>vantōr palarē vampa vēntar</l>
<l>piṭiyuyirp pṉṉa kaikkava rirumpi</l>
<l>ṉōvuṟa ḻirumpuṟaṅ kāvaṟ kaṇṇik</l>
<l>karuṅkaṇ koṇṭa neruṅkal vēmulai</l>
<l>maiya ṉōkkiṟ ṟaiyalai nayantō</l>
<l>raḷiyar tāmēyiva ṭaṉṉai mārē</l>
<l>celvam vēṇṭār cerupukal vēṇṭi</l>
<l>niralal lōrkkut taralō villeṉak</l>
<l>kaḻippiṇip palakaiyar katuvāy vāḷar</l>
<l>kuḻāaṅ koṇṭa kurutiyam pulavoṭu</l>
<l>kaḻāat talaiyar karuṅkaṭai neṭuvē</l>
<l>liṉṉa maṟavart tāyiṉu maṉṉō</l>
<l>veṉṉā vatuko ṟāṉē</l>
<l>paṉṉal vēliyip paṇainnal lūrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>When the elephant bulls were tied, the groves were stirred up,</l>
<l>when the chariots ran, the streets were full of dust,</l>
<l>by the horses’ turning about, the roads got confused,</l>
<l>by the vessels’ being washed, the harbours fell in chaos,</l>
<l>many were those who came,</l>
<l>for the ground to bend as the burden increased</l>
<l>by the mass of seats for wrathful warriors.</l>
<l>          A new king</l>
<l>is yearning for the woman, with voluptuous looks:</l>
<l>[her] firm(?) hot breasts taken in with [his] black eyes,</l>
<l>aiming at the big rear guard close to pain</l>
<l>from the iron seized by [his] hand, like the sigh of an elephant cow. (?!)</l>
<l>To be pitied are her people:</l>
<l>not caring for riches they wanted to enter a fight,</l>
<l>saying “as for giving [her away] to someone out of the order, no!”</l>
<l>they with shields tied from bamboo, they with jagged swords,</l>
<l>their heads unwashed, long spears with black tips</l>
<l>– even if it has warriors of that type, alas,</l>
<l>what will become of it,</l>
<l>this good village of fields with cotton hedges?  </l>
</lg>
